---
title: Old Bay Buttered-Up Chicken with Garlic Broccoli & Roasted Veggies
description: Whipping up a compound butter is one of our favorite ways to add big flavor to any dish. Here, we blend the butter with Old Bay Seasoning, then dollop it over seared chicken for rich, smoky, peppery notes. It’s finished with a scallion pan sauce, then paired with sides of roasted green beans and carrots and creamy, garlicky mashed potatoes. A word to the wise: Try topping your still-warm potatoes with a bit of the butter for a truly epic bite.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/67325f021cd01ca44ffc2be3-175b7322.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/67350cee46194b512b40731d-en-US.pdf
servings: 2
nutrition:
  calories: 610 kcal
  fat: 41 g
  saturated fat: 18 g
  carbohydrates: 27 g
  sugar: 11 g
  protein: 39 g
  fiber: 8 g
  sodium: 1200 mg
cuisine: North America
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/old-bay-buttered-up-chicken-67350cee46194b512b40731d
author: HelloFresh
course: main course
time required: 40 minutes
---

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Place @butter{2%tbsp} in a small #microwave-safe bowl{}; bring to room temperature.

Dice @potatoes{12%oz} into 1⁄2-inch pieces. Peel @garlic{1%clove}. Trim, peel, and halve @carrots{6%oz} lengthwise; slice into green-bean-size pieces. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens.

Cut @broccoli{8%oz} into bite-size pieces if necessary. Peel and mince garlic. (Save potatoes for another use.)

Place potatoes and garlic in a medium #pot with enough salted water to cover by 2 inches. Bring to a boil and cook until potatoes are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Reserve 1⁄2 cup potato cooking liquid, then drain and return potatoes to pot.

Mash potatoes with @sour cream{1.5%tbsp} and @plain butter{1%tbsp} until smooth, adding splashes of reserved potato cooking liquid as needed. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> Swap in broccoli for potatoes and garlic; cook 2-4 minutes. (No need to reserve cooking liquid.) Drain, then return broccoli to pot. Toss with @plain butter{1%tbsp} and minced garlic. Season with salt and pepper. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve. (Save sour cream for another use.)

While potatoes cook, trim @green beans{6%oz} if necessary. Toss carrots and green beans on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @cooking oil{}, salt, and pepper.

Roast on top rack until veggies are tender, ~{15-20%minutes}.

Meanwhile, to #bowl{} with softened butter, add 1⁄2 tsp @Old Bay Seasoning{1/2%tsp} and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste; mix to combine.

> If butter is not yet softened, microwave for 10 seconds.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @Old Bay Seasoning{1%tsp}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites; cook, stirring, until softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit} and 1⁄4 cup @water{1/4%cup}. Simmer until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat and stir in @plain butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

If necessary, reheat mashed potatoes with a splash of potato cooking liquid over low heat for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Divide mashed potatoes, chicken, and veggies between plates. Top chicken with pan sauce, then dollop with Old Bay butter. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Top potatoes with some of the sauce or Old Bay butter if you like!

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.